<subSubSection id="1D88C1DD0135FFD8FF6AF9FFFC93F960" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="552D92560135FFD8FF6AF9FFFC93F960" blockId="2.[136,1452,1631,2090]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="67E64E440135FFD8FF6AF9FFFE36F987" bold="true" box="[189,462,1631,1658]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Life mode and habitat:</emphasis>
—saprotrophic species found on dead bark of 
<taxonomicName id="9292E9D50135FFD8FC19F9C0FB61F987" box="[974,1177,1631,1657]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Burseraceae" genus="Bursera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simaruba">
<emphasis id="67E64E440135FFD8FC19F9C0FB61F987" box="[974,1177,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Bursera simaruba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Sarg. (
<taxonomicName id="9292E9D50135FFD8FAC0F9C0FA5BF984" box="[1303,1443,1632,1658]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Burseraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Burseraceae</taxonomicName>
) and on decaying rachises and petioles of 
<taxonomicName id="9292E9D50135FFD8FD83F924FD2DF963" box="[596,725,1667,1693]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Euterpe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oleracea">
<emphasis id="67E64E440135FFD8FD83F924FD2DF963" box="[596,725,1667,1693]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">E. oleracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="9292E9D50135FFD8FD34F924FCA7F960" box="[739,863,1668,1694]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Arecaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1D88C1DD0135FFD8FF6AF907FBABF93F" box="[189,1107,1703,1730]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="552D92560135FFD8FF6AF907FBABF93F" blockId="2.[136,1452,1631,2090]" box="[189,1107,1703,1730]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="67E64E440135FFD8FF6AF907FEA1F93F" bold="true" box="[189,345,1703,1729]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<collectingCountry id="2D85D2C60135FFD8FEA1F907FE49F93F" box="[374,433,1703,1729]" name="Cuba" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Cuba</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3103EFA70135FFD8FE69F907FD4DF93C" author="Castaneda-Ruiz, R. F." box="[446,693,1703,1730]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" pagination="57 - 87" refId="ref2576" refString="Castaneda-Ruiz, R. F. (1984) Nuevos taxones de Deuteromycotina: Arnoldiella robusta gen. et sp. nov., Roigiella lignicola gen. et sp. nov., Sporidesmium pseudolmediae sp. nov. y Thozetella havanensis sp. nov. Revista del Jardin Botanico Nacional Universidad de la Habana 5 (1): 57 - 87. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 3 - 319 - 29137 - 6 _ 9" type="journal article" year="1984">Castañeda-Ruiz 1984</bibRefCitation>
). Cited for the first time from 
<collectingCountry id="2D85D2C60135FFD8FBD0F907FBB7F93F" box="[1031,1103,1703,1729]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1D88C1DD0135FFD8FF6AF96CFA73F7D7" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="552D92560135FFD8FF6AF96CFA73F7D7" blockId="2.[136,1452,1631,2090]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis id="67E64E440135FFD8FF6AF96CFEF1F918" bold="true" box="[189,265,1740,1766]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Notes:</emphasis>
—According to literature, 
<taxonomicName id="9292E9D50135FFD8FDECF96CFD3AF91B" box="[571,706,1739,1765]" genus="Mycelephas" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="67E64E440135FFD8FDECF96CFD3AF91B" box="[571,706,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">M. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is regarded as a rare species with a restricted distribution to the place of collection of the 
<typeStatus id="8A292CF40135FFD8FE7DF94FFDE8F8F7" box="[426,528,1775,1801]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">holotype</typeStatus>
. This species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="9292E9D50135FFD8FCECF950FC2DF8F7" box="[827,981,1775,1801]" genus="Mycelephas" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="levisporus">
<emphasis id="67E64E440135FFD8FCECF950FC2DF8F7" box="[827,981,1775,1801]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">M. levisporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by smaller and rugose conidia with more septa (6–11) (
<bibRefCitation id="3103EFA70135FFD8FEF4F8B3FDE1F8D0" author="Castaneda-Ruiz, R. F." box="[291,537,1811,1838]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" pagination="57 - 87" refId="ref2576" refString="Castaneda-Ruiz, R. F. (1984) Nuevos taxones de Deuteromycotina: Arnoldiella robusta gen. et sp. nov., Roigiella lignicola gen. et sp. nov., Sporidesmium pseudolmediae sp. nov. y Thozetella havanensis sp. nov. Revista del Jardin Botanico Nacional Universidad de la Habana 5 (1): 57 - 87. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 3 - 319 - 29137 - 6 _ 9" type="journal article" year="1984">Castañeda-Ruiz 1984</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="3103EFA70135FFD8FDF2F8B3FCB5F8D0" author="Cantillo-Perez, T. &amp; Mena-Portales, J. &amp; Gusmao, L. F. P." box="[549,845,1811,1838]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" pagination="5 - 8" refId="ref2520" refString="Cantillo-Perez, T., Mena-Portales, J. &amp; Gusmao, L. F. P. (2017) Mycelephas levisporus sp. nov. on submerged wood from a freshwater habitat in Brazil. Mycotaxon 132: 5 - 8. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.5248 / 132.5" type="journal article" year="2017">
Cantillo-Pérez 
<emphasis id="67E64E440135FFD8FD18F8B4FCF9F8D3" box="[719,769,1811,1837]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). The Brazilian specimens showed conidiophores and conidiogenous cells with larger dimensions than those recorded for the Cuban collection. Conidia were also slightly larger in relation to the type material, but had fewer septa. The differences in dimensions reflect the substrates and environmental conditions where the specimens were collected (
<tableCitation id="1810A7ED0135FFD8FC82F8DFFC51F864" box="[853,937,1919,1946]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,224,904,930]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="TABLE 1. Dimensional variations of conidiophores, conidiogenous cells, and conidia of Mycelephas species (minimum and maximum values of length and width)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/01EDC2DE0134FFD9FF5FFC28F8A6FC5C" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" tableUuid="01EDC2DE0134FFD9FF5FFC28F8A6FC5C">Table 1</tableCitation>
). Unfortunately, it was not possible to obtain cultures of 
<taxonomicName id="9292E9D50135FFD8FEDFF804FE76F843" box="[264,398,1955,1981]" genus="Mycelephas" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="67E64E440135FFD8FEDFF804FE76F843" box="[264,398,1955,1981]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">M. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this study. 
<bibRefCitation id="3103EFA70135FFD8FDF8F803FCCBF840" author="Castaneda-Ruiz, R. F." box="[559,819,1955,1982]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" pagination="57 - 87" refId="ref2576" refString="Castaneda-Ruiz, R. F. (1984) Nuevos taxones de Deuteromycotina: Arnoldiella robusta gen. et sp. nov., Roigiella lignicola gen. et sp. nov., Sporidesmium pseudolmediae sp. nov. y Thozetella havanensis sp. nov. Revista del Jardin Botanico Nacional Universidad de la Habana 5 (1): 57 - 87. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 3 - 319 - 29137 - 6 _ 9" type="journal article" year="1984">Castañeda-Ruiz (1984)</bibRefCitation>
obtained colonies of this fungus on cornmeal agar with similar dimensions to those of the material on natural substrate (
<tableCitation id="1810A7ED0135FFD8FCA2F867FC34F81C" box="[885,972,1991,2018]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,224,904,930]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="TABLE 1. Dimensional variations of conidiophores, conidiogenous cells, and conidia of Mycelephas species (minimum and maximum values of length and width)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/01EDC2DE0134FFD9FF5FFC28F8A6FC5C" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" tableUuid="01EDC2DE0134FFD9FF5FFC28F8A6FC5C">Table 1</tableCitation>
). Some differences are perceptible in the morphology of conidia of 
<taxonomicName id="9292E9D50135FFD8FE70F84CFDD2F7FB" box="[423,554,2027,2053]" genus="Mycelephas" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="67E64E440135FFD8FE70F84CFDD2F7FB" box="[423,554,2027,2053]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">M. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in pure culture being less compact and having smaller filaments. The illustrations and photomicrographs presented by 
<bibRefCitation id="3103EFA70135FFD8FDF7F7AFFCDAF7D4" author="Castaneda-Ruiz, R. F." box="[544,802,2063,2090]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" pagination="57 - 87" refId="ref2576" refString="Castaneda-Ruiz, R. F. (1984) Nuevos taxones de Deuteromycotina: Arnoldiella robusta gen. et sp. nov., Roigiella lignicola gen. et sp. nov., Sporidesmium pseudolmediae sp. nov. y Thozetella havanensis sp. nov. Revista del Jardin Botanico Nacional Universidad de la Habana 5 (1): 57 - 87. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 3 - 319 - 29137 - 6 _ 9" type="journal article" year="1984">Castañeda-Ruiz (1984)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="3103EFA70135FFD8FC8EF7B0FBD3F7D4" author="Gams, W. &amp; Seifert, K. A. &amp; Morgan-Jones, G." box="[857,1067,2063,2090]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" pagination="89 - 108" refId="ref2910" refString="Gams, W., Seifert, K. A. &amp; Morgan-Jones, G. (2009) New and validated hyphomycete taxa to resolve nomenclatural and taxonomic issues. Mycotaxon 110: 89 - 108. https: // doi. org / 10.5248 / 110.89" type="journal article" year="2009">
Gams 
<emphasis id="67E64E440135FFD8FC76F7B0FC2AF7D7" box="[929,978,2063,2089]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">et al</emphasis>
. (2009)
</bibRefCitation>
clearly show these differences.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
